We are seeking for a Project Coordinator to help the team collaborate at every stage of the development process: gathering and clarifying feature requirements, collaborating on execution options and tradeoffs, and delivering features on schedule without crunching. In this highly collaborative role, you are responsible for the coordination and management of several CGI projects in development and recently deployed. Your daily tasks will involve administration, coordination, and a lot of problem-solving while providing day-to-day support to the Creative Operations and the 3D/2D Team.
About the Role
Work with the CGI Team, the Head of Production, and the Studio Manager to achieve the company s goals objectives
Help maintain high-level artifacts that keep the team aligned and moving forward together: team calendars, project roadmaps, and team trackers
Schedule, plan, and facilitate a variety of team meetings: kickoff meetings, team assembly meetings, general meetings, and follow-up meetings;
Manage issue tracking for teams: clarify issues, clean backlogs, create helpful filters, and maintain useful dashboards;
Work and manage vendors to ensure the quality of productions.
About You
Minimum +2 years experience, in Post-production/ 3D Production / Gaming production or coordinating
Understanding of the creative video development cycle from pre-production to post-production delivery
Background in the VFX field is considered a plus;
Experience working with a multi-discipline software team in a project management capacity
Knowledge of balancing technical requirements, product vision, and schedule
Knowledge of Click up/ Monday/ Asana/ Trello System-High level of English is a must;
Knowledge of Adobe Creative Cloud / 3D Software is considered a plus-Passion for games, animation, and the 3D field;
Mobile game development, publishing, and/or live operations experience are a plus;
Ability to prioritize projects to meet deadlines.
Ability to work in a global environment
Excellent communication and problem-solving skills
